           <div class="panel-pane pane-block pane-block-191">
            <h2 class="pane-title">
             HMS Bioethics Journal
            </h2>
            <div class="pane-content">
             <p>
              Original articles, video, and commentary about moral values inherent in clinical practice, biomedical, research, and health policy.
             </p>
             <p>
              <a href="http://bioethicsjournal.hms.harvard.edu/" target="_blank">
               Read the latest issue.
              </a>
             </p>
             <p>
              <a href="http://bioethicsjournal.hms.harvard.edu/" target="_blank">
               <img alt="HMS Bioethics Journal" src="/sites/g/files/mcu336/f/img/2017-08-ClinicalEthics-BlockLogo.jpg" style="width: 209px; height: 209px;"/>
              </a>
             </p>
             <p>
              <a href="http://bioethicsjournal.hms.harvard.edu/" target="_blank">
               <em>
                <strong>
                 HMS Bioethics Journal
                </strong>
               </em>
              </a>
              <br/>
              Informed Ethical Dialogue in Morally Challenging Times
             </p>
            </div>
           </div>
           <div class="panel-pane pane-block pane-block-41">
            <div class="pane-content">
             <h2 style="border-bottom: 1px solid #c1bab5; padding-bottom: 10px; font-weight: bold; font-size: 14p; line-height: 18px; letter-spacing: 0.035em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #35312d;">
              OUR MISSION
             </h2>
             <p>
              Harvard Medical School launched the Center for Bioethics out of the conviction that we have a particular responsibility to ensure that values and ethics are always part of medical training, laboratory and clinical research, and ongoing professional education. ​
              <a href="http://bioethics.hms.harvard.edu/about-us">
               Learn more »
              </a>
             </p>
             <p>
             </p>
